injuries.long_comment: The extension includes a player option for the 2027-28 season. Mitchell's future with the Cavaliers has been a major storyline in the media for well over a year, so Cleveland will be relieved to secure Mitchell's signature as they move into a new era with coach Kenny Atkinson at the helm. During the regular season in 2023-24, Mitchell averaged 26.6 points, 6.1 assists, 5.1 rebounds, 1.8 steals and 3.3 three-pointers.
injuries.short_comment: Mitchell (calf) and the Cavaliers agreed to a three-year, $150.3 million extension Tuesday, ESPN's Adrian Wojnarowski reports.

injuries.long_comment: Several Mavericks are practicing together in Los Angeles this week, including new addition Klay Thompson. Irving is with the group, but he's not participating in any scrimmages yet while working his way back from offseason hand surgery. Dallas made a surprise run to the NBA Finals last year but fizzled out and looked overmatched against Boston. A healthy Irving will be key if the Mavericks hope to replicate their success in 2024-25, so don't be surprised if he's limited to begin preseason work as a precaution. Irving averaged 25.6 points, 5.2 assists, 5.0 rebounds and 1.3 steals in 35.0 minutes across 58 appearances during his first full season with Dallas last year.
injuries.short_comment: Irving (hand) has been cleared for limited work during the offseason and remains on track for the start of training camp, NBA writer Marc Stein reports.

injuries.long_comment: Markkanen renegotiated his 2024-25 salary as well, earning himself another $24 million. With this extension, Markkanen will not be eligible to be moved prior to the Feb. 6 trade deadline, so it's clear that the forward is in this for the long haul with Utah. Markkanen will be a very popular target early on in fantasy drafts after averaging 23.2 points, 8.2 rebounds, 2.0 assists and 3.2 three-pointers during the 2023-24 regular season.
injuries.short_comment: Marrkanen (shoulder) signed a five-year, $238 million contract extension with the Jazz on Wednesday, ESPN's Adrian Wojnarowski reports.

injuries.long_comment: While Leonard will be limited to strengthening his knee during training camp, there is optimism within the Clippers that the surgery has helped progress the star forward's recovery. It is still unclear whether or not Leonard will be fully good to go once the regular season rolls around.
injuries.short_comment: Leonard underwent offseason surgery to address swelling in his knee, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Stevens did not provide an updated timetable for Porzingis, but he said he's been surprised with how quick he's improving. The Celtics originally gave Porzingis a 5-to-6 month timetable, and the center told ESPN's Ramona Shelburne that he's expecting to return in December. With Porzingis trending in the right direction, he'll offer plenty of appeal as a stash pick in fantasy drafts.
injuries.short_comment: Brad Stevens said that Porzingis (foot) is making good progress since his foot surgery back in June, Jared Weiss of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Bridges will return to the Hornets after averaging a career-high 21.0 points, 7.3 rebounds and 3.3 assists across 69 regular-season games. The 26-year-old also shot a career-high 6.5 attempts from deep in 2023-24 on 34.9 percent from range. Bridges missed the Hornets' final game with a wrist injury; however, he is expected to be ready for training camp.
injuries.short_comment: The Hornets re-signed Bridges (wrist) to a three-year, $75 million deal Saturday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.

injuries.long_comment: Vassell will more-than-likely miss the start of the 2024-25 season due to a lingering foot injury. The 24-year-old was shut down in the beginning of April after averaging a career-high 19.5 points, 4.1 assists, 3.8 rebounds and 1.1 steals across 33.1 minutes per game in 68 regular-season outings. In Vassell's absence, Stephon Castle and Malaki Branham are both candidates to pick up extra playing time.
injuries.short_comment: Vassell is not expected to return to game action until early November due to a stress reaction in his right foot which ended his 2023-24 campaign early, Jeff Garcia of KENS 5 San Antonio reports.

injuries.long_comment: Williams played just 19 games in the 2022-2023 season due to a back injury. He was seemingly on track for a healthy training camp prior to this new injury. The big man projects to start at center for Charlotte when healthy, but it now looks like he will miss most of training camp. Look for the Hornets to err on the side of caution with the big man in order to avoid another season of a lingering injury.
injuries.short_comment: Williams (back) has suffered a tendon strain in his left foot and will be re-evaluated in two weeks, Tim Bontemps of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Middleton underwent procedures on both ankles during the offseason, but he hasn't been cleared for five-on-five action yet, meaning the team will take a cautious approach to his recovery process. With training camp commencing Oct. 1, the Bucks want to do everything possible to ensure Middleton will be available for the start of the regular season in late October. Middleton was limited to 55 games in the 2023-24 regular season and produced averages of 15.1 points, 4.7 rebounds, 5.3 assists and 1.7 three-pointers per contest.
injuries.short_comment: Middleton (ankle) will be limited once training camp starts on Oct. 1, Chris Haynes of Turner Sports reports.

injuries.long_comment: Hendricks showed some signs of growth in his second Summer League stint but remained inconsistent on the offensive end. Still, Hendricks should be given plenty of time to work through growing pains during the regular season with the Jazz still in a rebuilding phase.
injuries.short_comment: Hendricks (personal) isn't with the Jazz for the team's exhibition game against Detroit on Sunday.

injuries.long_comment: The Twin Cities have a new pair of twin towers to hold down its frontcourt. Randle's fifth year in New York was plagued with injuries, which led him to play just 46 games in the 2023-24 season. The veteran big man underwent surgery on his right shoulder in April and was given a five-month re-Evaluation timetable. It remains to be seen how close he is to being ready for the start of the season.
injuries.short_comment: Randle (shoulder) has been dealt to the Timberwolves along with Donte DiVincenzo in exchance for Karl-Anthony Towns, Shams Charania of The Athletic

injuries.long_comment: Allen is expected to retreat to the bench in favor of Jones, who will start in the backcourt alongside Devin Booker. Allen made 75 regular-season appearances (74 starts) last season, during which he averaged 13.5 points, 3.9 rebounds and 3.5 assists across 33.5 minutes per game. The 28-year-old also shot a career-high 46.1 percent from three-point range last season, and he will more-than-likely serve as a crucial spark off the bench.
injuries.short_comment: Coach Mike Budenholzer said Friday that Tyus Jones will begin the year in the starting five, leaving Allen (ankle) to come off the bench, Duane Rankin of The Arizona Republic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Thompson's rookie season was cut short in March due to undergoing treatment for a blood clot, during which he averaged 8.8 points, 6.4 rebounds, 1.9 assists and 1.1 steals across 25.1 minutes in 63 regular-season games. The Pistons are likely playing it safe with the 21-year-old, as he is expected to ramp up on-court activity during the summer, and be ready for training camp in the Fall.
injuries.short_comment: Thompson is not set to participate in the Summer League while being treated for a blood clot, James L. Edwards III of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Brown will be re-evaluated in three weeks, meaning he is more than likely to be held out of the team's preseason opener against the Wizards on Oct. 6. The 28-year-old said that the lingering knee issue affected his play starting in December of last season, during which he averaged 10.8 points, 4.2 rebounds and 2.9 assists across 27.9 minutes in 67 appearances (44 starts). If Brown misses additional time, Gradey Dick (ankle) will likely pick up extra minutes and could secure the starting job.
injuries.short_comment: The Raptors announced Brown underwent arthroscopic surgery on his right knee, and he will be re-evaluated in three weeks, Ryan Wolstat of the Toronto Sun reports.

injuries.long_comment: Robinson is coming off two procedures on his left ankle, with the most recent surgery taking place on May 14. According to Begley, a return in December or January could be on the table depending on how the rehab process goes, as neither Robinson or the Knicks want to rush the process to make sure that the center is at full strength before getting clearance. With Robinson sidelined to begin the season, Julius Randle could spend a lot of time at center in smaller lineups, while Precious Achiuwa and Jericho Sims will have a lot more opportunity to earn meaningful minutes.
injuries.short_comment: Robinson (ankle) will not be ready for the beginning of the NBA season, Ian Begley of SportsNet New York reports.

injuries.long_comment: Edey tweaked his right ankle during Thursday's win over the Pelicans. While the issue is expected to be minor, it's unsurprising to see Memphis proceed with caution. Edey, the No. 9 overall pick in the 2024 NBA Draft, is expected to compete for a rotational role in Memphis' frontcourt as a rookie.
injuries.short_comment: Edey (ankle) has been shut down for the remainder of Summer League, Drew Hill of The Daily Memphian reports.

injuries.long_comment: Williams indicated earlier this summer that he was fully recovered from his February foot surgery and was pain-free, but he experienced a setback during the team's offseason activities. He signed a five-year deal with the Bulls in late June, but it's not yet clear whether his recent discomfort will impact his availability for the start of training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Williams experienced foot discomfort during the Bulls' recent minicamp and has required additional rest in recent weeks, Darnell Mayberry of The Athletic reported Monday.

injuries.long_comment: A draft-and-stash player from the 2022 NBA Draft, Matkovic joined the Pelicans' G League affiliate late in the 2023-24 season and has been part of the team's Summer League roster in Las Vegas. With the Pelicans a bit thin in the frontcourt, Matkovic could see occasional playing time during the upcoming season. His groin injury shouldn't impact his availability for training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Matkovic won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against the Nuggets due to left groin soreness, Will Guillory of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Huerter is recovering from a shoulder procedure he underwent in early April, and the sharpshooting guard has been cleared for on-court workouts, meaning he's trending in the right direction. Huerter will be re-evaluated in mid-October, and if everything continues to trend in the right direction, he could be cleared for full contact activity before the start of the 2024-25 regular season.
injuries.short_comment: Huerter (shoulder) has been cleared for on-court workouts, Deuce Mason of NBC Sports California reports.

injuries.long_comment: The Grizzlies allowed Kennard to hit free agency when they declined his team option on June 29, but there was always mutual interest to get a new deal done. Kennard is a valuable floor spacer for the Grizzlies, especially when playing alongside Ja Morant and Desmond Bane. During the 2023-24 regular season, Kennard drained 45 percent of his three-point attempts. He did miss time at the end of the campaign with a troublesome left knee issue, and that will be an injury to monitor ahead of training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Kennard (knee) and the Grizzlies agreed to a one-year, $11 million deal Wednesday, ESPN's Adrian Wojnarowski reports.

injuries.long_comment: Pelinka added that Vanderbilt had a lingering bone spur that was also cleared up during the procedures, which happened right after the 2023-24 season concluded. Vanderbilt was a key piece during the Lakers' run to the Western Conference Finals two years ago, but last season, the forward struggled to stay on the court, making just 29 regular-season appearances. Vanderbilt brings a defensive versatility that is hard to come by and will certainly have a role if he's healthy on Opening Night, though probably not one worth fantasy relevance outside of deeper leagues prioritizing defensive stats.
injuries.short_comment: General manager Rob Pelinka said Wednesday that Vanderbilt had successful procedures on both feet this offseason, and there's optimism the forward will be ready for Opening Night against the Timberwolves on Oct. 22, Dave McMenamin of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: A shoulder injury in February led to a premature ending to Richardson's season, but he was a rotational player prior to the injury. Overall, he averaged 9.9 points, 2.8 rebounds, 2.4 rebounds, 2.4 assists, 0.6 steals and 1.5 triples across 25.7 minutes in 43 games. The veteran wing will look to earn a similar role for the Heat in the upcoming season.
injuries.short_comment: Richardson 9shoulder) has picked up his $3 million player option to return for the 2024-25 season, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Risacher will miss the Hawks' final Summer League contest -- his third consecutive absence -- due to a bruised right quad. The issue isn't expected to have any long term ramifications and it's likely that Risacher will be a full go for training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Risacher (quadriceps) won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against the Knicks, Brad Rowland of the Locked On Podcast Network reports.

injuries.long_comment: Watson's injury being described as "minor" indicates that he isn't in danger of missing any regular-season action. The 22-year-old forward is expected to be a primary backup in Denver's forward rotation this season.
injuries.short_comment: Watson didn't participate in Thursday's practice due to minor hamstring discomfort, Adam Mares of DenverStiffs.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: The Trail Blazers drafted Deandre Ayton's backup in Donovan Clingan this summer, so Williams no longer makes a ton of sense on the Portland roster. He will need to show he's healthy before another team will be willing to take the plunge on the oft-injured big man, but getting out of Portland could only be good for his fantasy outlook. The Pelicans have also been rumored to be interested in acquiring the Time Lord, and that would be an excellent landing spot for him in terms of fantasy hoops, but to be clear, nothing is imminent on the Williams trade front.
injuries.short_comment: The Kings have expressed interest in Williams, Brett Siegel of Clutch Points reports.

injuries.long_comment: While Williams is expected to make a full recovery, he will almost certainly miss all of training camp and the preseason. The 24-year-old forward could remain sidelined for Memphis' regular-season opener on Oct. 23 against Utah. Williams is slated to be one of the Grizzlies' top forward options off the bench when healthy this season.
injuries.short_comment: The Grizzlies announced Thursday that imaging has revealed a stress reaction in the upper portion of Williams' tibia and he will be re-evaluated in approximately four weeks.

injuries.long_comment: While Bogdanovic underwent successful surgeries on his left foot and left wrist this offseason, he will be limited in action to begin Brooklyn's training camp. However, the veteran forward was able to compete in an exhibition game earlier in September, so there is a chance he will be ready to go once the regular season rolls around.
injuries.short_comment: Bogdanovic (wrist/foot) will not be ready to go for the beginning of training camp, Brian Lewis of the New York Post reports.

injuries.long_comment: This is a massive hurdle for Ball to clear. The 2017 No. 2 overall pick hasn't played in an NBA game since Jan. 14, 2022, and has undergone three surgeries on his left knee during that stretch, including an experimental cartilage transplant for a new meniscus. Cowley notes that no professional athlete has ever returned to high-level competition after having that surgery. Ball picked up his $21.4 million player option for 2024-25, so the Bulls would certainly be incentivized to play him if he's healthy. However, it's unclear how he'll fit into Chicago's plans after trading for Josh Giddey this offseason.
injuries.short_comment: The Bulls confirmed Wednesday that Ball (knee) has started playing in full-contact five-on-five scrimmages and hasn't faced any setbacks, Joe Cowley of the Chicago Sun-Times reports.

injuries.long_comment: The forward will be re-evaluated in eight weeks, meaning he will miss the start of the 2024-25 season. This is a tough blow for Wood, as it will set him back with his offseason training. Wood exercised his $3.04 million player option back in May and was already facing an uphill battle for playing time, and this certainly won't help.
injuries.short_comment: Wood underwent a successful arthroscopic surgical procedure on his left knee Monday, Mike Trudell of Spectrum SportsNet reports.

injuries.long_comment: Jackson will miss at least the first month of the season while rehabbing from the procedure but is expected to make a full recovery. However, when healthy, his role remains unclear. As a rookie, the second-round pick carved out a substantial role for the injury-riddled Grizzlies. Over his final 18 regular-season appearances, Jackson averaged 20.4 points, 5.0 rebounds and 2.1 assists in 34.1 minutes per game. With Ja Morant (shoulder), Marcus Smart (finger) and Desmond Bane (back) returning to full strength this offseason, Jackson will have a difficult time repeating those numbers in Year 2.
injuries.short_comment: Jackson underwent a successful procedure to repair a broken fifth metatarsal in his right foot Wednesday and will be evaluated in approximately three months.

injuries.long_comment: Sensabaugh had three points, two assists and two rebounds for the Jazz before leaving Saturday's game for good. Despite this setback, Sensabaugh is likely to be 100 percent recovered in time for training camp. Heading into his second season, Sensabaugh could be a rotation player for the Jazz right out of the gate.
injuries.short_comment: Sensabaugh will miss at least six weeks after tearing an extensor tendon in his left middle finger Saturday during the Summer League, Ryan Miller of KSL.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: When healthy, Lyles projects to provide frontrcourt depth this season in Sacramento behind Domantas Sabonis and Alex Len. Thus, he looks to be a fringe-rotational player. His timeline for recovery should lead to his return prior to the regular-season tipping off assuming he avoids any setbacks. However, he may be behind on his conditioning at that point.
injuries.short_comment: Lyles suffered a left groin strain during offseason workouts and is expected to be sidelined three weeks, James Ham of ESPN 1320 Sacramento reports.

injuries.long_comment: Dick played well in Summer League action but will be forced to miss the finale due to a right ankle sprain. The injury does not figure to linger into training camp, let alone the regular season. The 20-year-old is primed for a significant role for a Raptors team looking to build for the future.
injuries.short_comment: Dick has been ruled Aaron Rose of SI.com for Sunday's Summer League game against the Spurs due to a right ankle sprain.

injuries.long_comment: Bey is coming off a down year in which he converted a career-low  31.6 percent of his three-point attempts across 63 games with the Hawks, but maybe a change of scenery will help him rediscover his sharpshooting ways. Unfortunately, he's still rehabbing from an ACL tear that he suffered in March, so it's unlikely he'll be ready for the start of the 2024-25 season.
injuries.short_comment: Bey has agreed to a three-year, $20 million contract with the Wizards, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.

injuries.long_comment: Castle injured his right wrist after a fall during Saturday's game against Portland, and he will remain sidelined for the remainder of Summer League as the Spurs play it safe with the fourth overall pick. Castle flashed the potential that made him a highly touted prospect in this year's draft during limited action in Summer League, putting up 22 points, five rebounds, four assists and a steal Saturday against the Trail Blazers. Castle will likely serve as a key player for San Antonio off the bench to begin the 2024-25 campaign.
injuries.short_comment: Castle suffered a right wrist sprain during Saturday's win over Portland and is out for the remainder of Summer League, Tom Orsborn of the San Antonio Express-News reports.

injuries.long_comment: Mogbo was selected by Toronto with the No. 31 overall pick in this year's draft, and he made two appearances during the Las Vegas Summer League, averaging 3.5 points and 3.5 rebounds in 12.9 minutes per game. He'll get a breather as the Raptors close out Summer League play Sunday.
injuries.short_comment: Mogbo has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League finale against the Spurs due to a back contusion, Aaron Rose of SI.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Williams made 51 appearances, including 15 starts, for the Grizzlies in 2023-24 before missing the remainder of the season with a right lower back injury and a hip flexor strain. Before going down to injury, the 22-year-old forward averaged 8.2 points, 3.5 rebounds and 1.5 assists in 20.4 minutes. However, efficiency was an issue, as he shot just 39.7 percent from the field and 30.7 percent from three. If Williams is able to enter the 2024-25 campaign healthy, he will likely compete for bench minutes in Brooklyn's forward rotation.
injuries.short_comment: The Grizzlies traded Williams (back/hip) and a 2030 second-round pick via Dallas to the Nets in exchange for Mamadi Diakite on Friday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.

injuries.long_comment: After missing the entire 2023-24 campaign with a knee injury, Lee will get another chance to prove his worth with the Suns. Back in 2022-23, Lee was a key rotation player for the Suns, averaging 8.2 points, 3.0 rebounds, 1.3 assists and 1.5 three-pointers while hitting 44.5 percent from beyond the arc.
injuries.short_comment: Lee (knee) and the Suns agreed to a one-year deal Wednesday, ESPN's Adrian Wojnarowski reports.

injuries.long_comment: Curry was dealt from the Mavs to the Hornets on Feb. 8 and averaged 9.0 points, 2.0 rebounds and 1.8 assists in his next eight appearances before being shut down for the rest of the year with an ankle injury. However, Curry evidently showed enough during his brief stint for the team to bring him back for the 2024-25 campaign. He'll face plenty of competition for playing time in Charlotte's backcourt, as he'll go up against the likes of Vasilije Micic, Tre Mann and Reggie Jackson.
injuries.short_comment: Curry (ankle) signed a one-year contract with the Hornets on Monday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.

injuries.long_comment: Carter sustained his left shoulder injury during a pre-draft workout, and the Kings were aware of the issue when selecting him with the 13th overall pick in the 2024 NBA Draft. The Kings announced Thursday that they'll update his status in approximately six months, so the 22-year-old will presumably miss at least the first few months of the 2024-25 season. However, Carter is expected to make a full recovery with no long-term concerns.
injuries.short_comment: The Kings announced Thursday that Carter underwent successful surgery to repair a torn labrum in his left shoulder, Jason Anderson of The Sacramento Bee reports.

injuries.long_comment: Reddish had the worst statistical year of his career in 2023-2024, during which he averaged 5.4 points, 2.1 rebounds, 1.0 assists and 1.0 steals across 20.5 minutes in 48 regular-season games. The 24-year-old has bounced around as of late, playing for four different teams over the last three years. Reddish has failed to live up to his draft stock, and he will hope to improve next season before becoming an unrestricted free agent in 2025-26.
injuries.short_comment: Reddish (ankle) exercised his $2.46 million player option for the 2024-25 season Saturday, Michael Scotto of USA Today reports.

injuries.long_comment: Agbaji appeared in Toronto's first four games during the Las Vegas Summer League but will sit out the finale. He averaged 6.0 points and 4.8 assists in 23.2 minutes per game over his four appearances.
injuries.short_comment: Agbaji has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League finale against the Spurs due to a right shin contusion, Aaron Rose of SI.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Bassey is still recovering from surgery to repair his torn left ACL in December but is expected to be healthy by the start of the regular season. However, the 24-year-old big man is unlikely to be a significant part of San Antonio's rotation in 2024-25.
injuries.short_comment: Bassey (knee) is expected to be limited in training camp but should be good to go for the Spurs' regular-season opener on Oct. 24 against Dallas, Jeff McDonald of the San Antonio Express-News reports.

injuries.long_comment: Hawkins underwent X-rays after sustaining the injury, which came back negative. Still, the Pelicans will refrain from putting the 22-year-old back into its final Summer League contest. Hawkins will finish the game with three points (0-3 FG, 3-4 FT) and a block across 11 minutes. It's unclear if the injury will impact Hawkins' availability for training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Hawkins has been ruled out for the remainder of Saturday's Summer League game against the Nuggets due to a right ankle injury.

injuries.long_comment: The timing of this is unfortunate for Williams with training camp right around the corner. A timetable was not provided by the Thunder, but Williams is scheduled to be re-evaluated at the end of the preseason. In 69 regular-season appearances for the Thunder in 2023-24, Williams averaged 4.7 points, 3.0 rebounds and 1.3 assists.
injuries.short_comment: Williams underwent a successful arthroscopic debridement procedure in his right knee Tuesday, Andrew Schlecht of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Fresh off inking a one-year deal over the summer, McLaughlin's start to the season will not be what he had in mind. When healthy, he is expected to compete with Keon Ellis for the backup point guard role behind De'Aaron Fox. The 28-year-old shot a career-best 47.2 percent from three-point range across 56 games in Minnesota last season to go along with 3.5 points and 1.3 rebounds across 11.2 minutes.
injuries.short_comment: McLaughlin sustained a grade 2 right ankle sprain during off-season workouts and will be re-evaluated in two weeks, James Ham of ESPN 1320 Sacramento reports.

injuries.long_comment: Missi won't suit up for the Pelicans' final Summer League contest as he tends to pain in his lower back. The 20-year-old flashed some of the rim protection and athleticism in Las Vegas that coaxed the Pelicans into selecting him with the 21st overall pick in this year's draft. He should be ready to go for training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Missi won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against the Nuggets due to lower back soreness, Will Guillory of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Fontecchio posted solid numbers with the Pistons and will get another chance to impress in Motor City. The 28-year-old was acquired by the Pistons via trade with the Jazz in February and averaged 15.4 points, 4.4 rebounds, 1.8 assists and 0.9 steals in 30.2 minutes for Detroit while starting in nine of 16 appearances. He's expected to be healthy come training camp in the fall.
injuries.short_comment: Fontecchio (toe) has re-signed with the Pistons on a two-year, $16 million deal, James L. Edwards III of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: Jackson saw a minimal role in his rookie year, averaging 2.2 points and 2.0 rebounds in 10.0 minutes across 57 appearances. While Jackson is expected to head into the 2024-25 campaign healthy, he will likely compete for depth minutes in Milwaukee's forward rotation yet again.
injuries.short_comment: The Bucks announced Friday that Jackson underwent successful surgery to repair a fracture of his left third finger that occurred during Tuesday's Summer League game against the Clippers but is expected to be a full participant in training camp.

injuries.long_comment: Dunn will sit out the Suns' final Summer League game due to pain in his left knee. The injury likely won't impact his training camp availability. The No. 28 overall pick in this year's draft flashed his defensive abilities during Summer League and is considered one of the best defenders in the 2024 rookie class.
injuries.short_comment: Dunn won't play in Saturday's game against the Kings due to left knee soreness, Duane Rankin of The Arizona Republic reports.

injuries.long_comment: While Bufkin's shoulder injury will keep him out of the Summer League, he is expected to make a full recovery ahead of training camp. The second-year guard averaged 4.8 points, 1.9 rebounds and 1.6 assists in 11.5 minutes across 17 appearances in 2023-24.
injuries.short_comment: The Hawks announced Thursday that Bufkin suffered a right shoulder subluxation during Tuesday's practice and will not play in the Las Vegas Summer League.

injuries.long_comment: The No. 10 overall pick in the 2024 NBA Draft, Williams played well in Summer League action but will miss the finale due to a minor ailment. He should be fully healthy for training camp and is expected to compete for a rotational role as a rookie.
injuries.short_comment: Williams has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League game against the Pistons due to an illness.

injuries.long_comment: Collier will take a seat for Utah's final exhibition game in Las Vegas due to pain in his right knee. The rookie point guard showed well during Summer League and could operate as Keyonte George's backup once the regular season rolls around.
injuries.short_comment: Collier (right knee soreness) won't play in Sunday's Summer League game against the Pistons.

injuries.long_comment: Bates-Diop was traded from the Nets to the Knicks earlier this offseason but will now return to Minnesota, where he started his NBA career back in 2018-19. Bates-Diop will likely compete for depth minutes in the Timberwolves' forward rotation.
injuries.short_comment: The Knicks traded Bates-Diop (shin) to the Timberwolves alongside Julius Randle (shoulder) and Donte DiVincenzo in a three-team deal that also sent DaQuan Jeffries to Charlotte, Jon Krawczynski of The Athletic reports.

injuries.long_comment: The first-round pick of the 2024 Draft will not be permitted to participate in on-court activities for at least a week of training camp due to the shoulder injury. However, Walter is not likely to miss any time in the regular-season, and the Raptors are expected to give an update on his status after one week. The 20-year-old played for Baylor in 2023-24, during which he averaged 14.5 points, 4.5 rebounds, 1.4 assists and 1.1 steals across 32.2 minutes per game in 35 regular-season appearances.
injuries.short_comment: Walter sprained his acromioclavicular joint (shoulder) during informal workouts and will not participate in on-court activities to start training camp, Tim Bontemps of ESPN.com reports.

injuries.long_comment: Preston will miss back-to-back games to end Summer League action due to personal reasons. The 2021 second-round pick signed a two-way contract with Utah this offseason after appearing in seven contests for the Jazz last season.
injuries.short_comment: Preston (personal) has been ruled out for Sunday's Summer League matchup against the Pistons.

injuries.long_comment: Cissoko made 12 regular-season appearances as a rookie, averaging 3.9 points and 1.9 rebounds in 11.8 minutes per game. His chances of competing for a role in the rotation in 2024-25 are slim, but if he doesn't crack the roster, then he should have a prominent role for the Austin Spurs in the G League.
injuries.short_comment: Cissoko (undisclosed) is listed in the Spurs roster ahead of training camp for the 2024-25 season.

injuries.long_comment: After waiving Bruno Fernando on Tuesday, the Hawks signed Barlow to a two-way pact. The move to sign the 21-year-old seemingly aligns with the club's plan to rebuild around their young core of Zaccharie Risacher (quad) and Jalen Johnson (ankle). However, Barlow may have a difficult time picking up minutes with the squad, buried behind Clint Capela, Onyeka Okongwu (toe), Larry Nance and Cody Zeller. Barlow spent two years with the Spurs, and in 2023-24 he averaged 3.8 points and 3.5 rebounds across 14.1 minutes in 29 regular-season games.
injuries.short_comment: The Hawks signed Barlow (knee) to a two-way contract on Tuesday, Adrian Wojnarowski of ESPN reports.

injuries.long_comment: The issue flared up during Thursday's game and the Nuggets will cautiously keep Pickett out of its Summer League Finale. The second-year guard should be healthy in time for training camp.
injuries.short_comment: Pickett won't play in Saturday's Summer League game against the Pelicans due to left groin soreness, Vinny Benedetto of The Denver Gazette reports.

injuries.long_comment: The Clippers declined Jones' team option in late June, but he'll rejoin the team and compete for a roster spot ahead of the 2024-25 campaign. The 23-year-old won't participate in Summer League play due to an ankle injury, and it's unclear whether he'll have limitations when training camp rolls around.
injuries.short_comment: Jones (ankle) agreed to a non-guaranteed deal with the Clippers on Friday, Shams Charania of The Athletic reports.
